events.name: LFP battery market trends
events.wd_description: The lithium iron phosphate (LFP) battery market has been growing due to its low cost, high safety, and long cycle life, particularly in vehicle use, utility-scale stationary applications, and backup power. Chinese manufacturers currently dominate the market, and the production is expected to rise, surpassing NMC batteries by 2028.

events.name: Market share and production trends
events.wd_description: As of September 2022, LFP battery market share for EVs reached 31%, with Tesla and Chinese EV maker BYD accounting for 68% of this share. Chinese manufacturers hold a near monopoly on LFP battery production.

events.wd_description: LFP batteries are less costly compared to NMC batteries and have better resource availability as they do not contain nickel or cobalt. They also raise fewer human rights and environmental concerns.
